{{Term|term= Quasi-realism |content= [[Quasi-realism]] }}{{defn|1= a [[non-cognitivism|non-cognitivist]], [[expressivism|expressivist]] meta-ethical and epistemological theory developed by professor [[Simon Blackburn]]. It holds that although propositions supervene on states of mind, they have many realist characteristics, such as only being able to change slowly or in response to changes in natural properties. }}

