== Z ==
{{Glossary}}

{{Term|term= Zen Buddhism |content= [[Zen Buddhism]] }}{{defn|1= A fusion of [[Mahayana]] [[Buddhism]] and [[Taoism]], practiced chiefly in China and Japan. It places great importance on moment-by-moment awareness and 'seeing deeply into the nature of things' by direct experience. The name derives from the Sanskrit word ''[[Dhyāna in Buddhism|dhyana]]'' referring to a particular [[meditation|meditative]] state. }}
{{Term|term= Zoroastrianism |content= [[Zoroastrianism]] }}{{defn|1= the religion and philosophy based on the teachings ascribed to the prophet [[Zoroaster]] (Zarathustra, Zartosht). }}

