'''Hierarchical epistemology''' is a [[theory of knowledge]] which posits that beings have different access to [[reality]] depending on their [[ontological]] rank.<ref>Jorge Ferrer, ''Revisiting Transpersonal Theory'', 2001, p. 76</ref>

